      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This DFHMSD macro (lines 19-25) defines the BMS map set named COPAU00. It specifies various attributes for the map set, including control options (ALARM, FREEKB), extended attributes (EXTATT=YES), the programming language (LANG=COBOL), input/output mode (MODE=INOUT), storage allocation (STORAGE=AUTO), terminal I/O area prefix (TIOAPFX=YES), and the map type (TYPE=&&SYSPARM). The TYPE parameter allows for different map types to be generated during compilation, such as a symbolic map or a physical map. This macro essentially acts as the container for all the individual map definitions within this BMS file, setting the overall context for how the screen will be handled by CICS.",
